Samuel Eto’o Fils, President of the Cameroonian Football Federation, has reacted to the victory of the Teranga Lions of Senegal at the just-concluded 2021 All African Cup of Nations, AFCON, in Cameroon. Eto congratulated the Senegalese side for winning the tournament hosted by his country, Cameroon. In a series of tweets on Monday, the former Barcelona legend said history was written with the just-concluded AFCON. Eto also applauded all teams that participated in the 2021 AFCON for giving their best. According to Eto: “This was #AFCON2021 It has been a true honour to have hosted such a legendary tournament in Cameroon. “Together, we’ve written history, forged friendships and demonstrated the unstoppable force that is African football. Congratulations to Senegal, our new African champions. “My deepest thanks to the competing teams for giving it your all, to the fans for your support, and to everyone involved in making this tournament happen. MERCI.” Senegal defeated Egypt to emerge winners of the latest edition of the biennial tournament in Cameroon.